snippet.textDisplay: That sucks that their dropping Optane memory. It no longer requires being on your boot drive so that means it can be used on any HDD or slow SSD. I have been enjoying it so far for my HDD which loads games just as fast as SSD as long as I play that game often enough that it does not get removed from the cache by being low priority. Well I hope cheaper 4 TB or more SSDs start coming out soon so that HDD would not be needed much anymore.

snippet.textDisplay:
In all honesty, several of us out there NEED low profile graphics cards. 
I ended up getting my mom's machine, which is a SFF computer, and it has NO room for even a low profile double size card. (right next to the power supply) 
I've had to use a 1030, which allows me to run games from like...5 years ago, and even FFxiv not to shabby, but anything greater results in 20 something FPS. It is good enough to run 4k video though, which is nice. 
2gb DDR is kinda lacking though. You'd think with DDR5 they could toss in 4gb.
